Three fixes for the Word document creation workflow reported by user.

1. office_run activate: run_applescript only added activate when wrapping
   scripts. Agent scripts include tell application but omit activate, so
   Word never launches. Fix: inject activate after the first tell line
   when missing.

2. Documents directory: container /workspace/Documents was mounted from
   workspace_dir, not from the per-agent documents dir that office.rs
   resolves. Agent creates files in the wrong location. Fix: bind-mount
   data_dir/{agent_id}/documents/ at /workspace/Documents.

3. XML tool calls: Qwen3.5-27b degrades to <parameter=...> format in
   long conversations. System silently ignored this, ending the turn.
   Fix: detect_malformed_tool_call() checks for the pattern after each
   response and injects a system hint message so the model retries.
